main event: A witness reported an observation of an Unidentified Flying Object in Columbus, Ohio on July 4, 1965.
interesting points: The report states that the name, address, and phone number of the witness were not received or returned.
The report concludes that there was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION'.
The report includes a questionnaire form for the witness to provide details about the UFO sighting, such as time, location, weather conditions, and description of the object.
The report mentions that the witness had previously reported the sighting to the Air Force on June 9, 1965.
The report includes a memo routing slip requesting an FTD Form 364 to be sent to the FTDSW/UFO in Columbus, Ohio regarding the UFO observation on July 4, 1967.
